args: Hngh! There's so many of them!
Quite so—but I've no intention of dying in\na place like this. HAAAH!
Now THAT'S the Naveed I know!
Urgh... Y-yeah, I'm okay. What about you?
Worry not about me; you're the one who\ntook that fearsome blow!
What were you thinking, diving between\nmyself and those fiends?
Heh. I guess I WASN'T thinking.\nMy body just moved on its own.
But we're both all right, which is what\nmatters.
This... Good heavens, this is it!
Wonder of wonders, it can be nothing else!\nYour actions are the very definition of a\ntrue and selfless love!
The true love I have been seeking has\nbeen inside you all along!
I'm uh...not really sure about that.
Poppycock! You are clearly the magnificent\nperson I've been seeking.
I wish to know you better, Prince.\nI wish to know your LOVE better.
To that end, I must know you down to\nyour very core. Might you grant me\nthis small boon?
You're basically saying you want to be\nbetter friends, right?
Well, that's certainly fine with me.
...Naveed? Think you can help me out\nwith some training?
Today I'm going to beat your lithomancy\nfor sure!
Ha ha! I think you'll find that no\nsimple endeavor.
But what say we sweeten the pot a bit?\nIf you can defeat me, I shall teach you\nthe secrets of my lithomancy.
Really? Well, I'm DEFINITELY going\nto win now.
Oh, it's Naveed and our fearless leader.\nWhat're they up to?
It's not that they're ＂up to＂ anything...
We were just noticing how much time the\ntwo of them have been spending together\nof late.
Indeed. These sparring sessions of theirs\nhave become a daily occurance.
But the relationship does not end there.\nThey also spend each and every mealtime\ntogether chattering like birds on a branch.
And just last night they were out all night\nin an attempt to find a flower that only\nblooms in the moonlight or somesuch.
Indeed. Did you not know that?
Spending all night with him makes me so\nvery jeaaaaaaaaa...errrr...ly. Yes. Jelly.\nJelly sounds splendid right now.
*sigh* I'll not begrudge His Highness a\nfriendship, but I fear this has gone a step\ntoo far.
{player_name} is our leader,\nwhich means his time must\nnaturally be spread quite thin.
He can ill afford to focus all of his\nattention on Naveed alone.
After all, I'm just as able a sparring\npartner as he—if not better!
And he should give a thought to those of\nus who prepare the nightly meal.
None of this is funny, you brute!
Heh. Yeah, okay. My bad. But listen,\nya don't gotta worry about any of this.
They're just a couple'a guys what found\na bit of chemistry.
Ya can't get mad at 'em for that.
Hell, Naveed up and asked to spend more\ntime with {player_name}.
So if that makes ya jealous, why not take a\npage from his book and do the same?
